194
00:34:55,679 --> 00:34:58,641
 Now, there is no competition

195
00:35:00,176 --> 00:35:09,721
between A and B. We don't say that, “You
got the first prize for coming out of the

196
00:35:09,746 --> 00:35:18,779
Sahastrara” (laughing) or we don't say,
“You have the second prize.” There's nothing

197
00:35:18,804 --> 00:35:29,672
like first, second in Sahaja Yoga, because
we are not running the race. There’s no

198
00:35:29,697 --> 00:35:37,297
competition between us. Whatever we are doing
is for our own satisfaction. Now think of

199
00:35:37,322 --> 00:35:43,226
something. There are five people who are running.
Now they have to think, out of these five

200
00:35:43,226 --> 00:35:53,644
people, who goes first. Here it is the other
way round: The five people are meditating;

201
00:35:53,886 --> 00:36:03,491
now everyone individually has to see for himself
if he satisfies himself or not, nobody else

202
00:36:03,516 --> 00:36:09,365
is going to give you a certificate. It is
you who has to give certificate to yourself,

203
00:36:09,365 --> 00:36:14,296
honestly. It's a very different position.

204
00:36:14,296 --> 00:36:24,977
It is you, your Sahastrara and your attention
and you have to see, within yourself, “How

205
00:36:25,002 --> 00:36:40,125
far have I realised my own powers, my own
compassion, my own personality?” You’ll

206
00:36:40,150 --> 00:36:50,961
have to test it yourself. It is you are the
one who decides. When you are the one who

207
00:36:50,986 --> 00:37:01,140
is running, it is you are the one who decides
without running, then what is the question

208
00:37:01,165 --> 00:37:12,809
of competition? The whole thing disappears
into nothing.

209
00:37:14,022 --> 00:37:23,942
As I told you the other day, an analogy that,
if you are looking at the mirror, then you

210
00:37:24,474 --> 00:37:33,657
are the one who is observing, your reflection
is the one that is observed and there is the

211
00:37:33,682 --> 00:37:44,361
action of seeing, so you are in 3 dimensions.
But supposing you become the mirror yourself,

212
00:37:48,520 --> 00:37:57,899
the whole process is reversed: You see yourself.
You don't have to see because you are seeing

213
00:37:57,924 --> 00:38:06,647
it all the time, it's just spontaneous. In
the same manner, when it comes to Sahastrara,

214
00:38:06,886 --> 00:38:14,672
it is your Sahastrara itself gives you the
full idea as to how you are. The diagnosis

215
00:38:14,697 --> 00:38:22,725
comes from your own Sahastrara. Your own Sahastrara
tells you what centres are catching because

216
00:38:22,750 --> 00:38:31,778
all the peethas of these seven centres are
in the Sahastrara. As if the Sahastrara is

217
00:38:31,806 --> 00:38:40,060
now watching yourself and reporting to you,
“See, this is wrong with you. This is wrong

218
00:38:40,085 --> 00:38:46,316
with you, this is wrong with you.” So, Sahastrara
being the best well-wisher that you have,

219
00:38:46,316 --> 00:38:52,986
gives you the right information about yourself,
so the best is that you correct yourself.

220
00:38:52,986 --> 00:39:02,465
So then, achieve that perfect state: that
is what you have to do. But once you have

221
00:39:02,490 --> 00:39:10,157
achieved the perfect state, you have achieved
your aim, you have no aim left. Like the lights

222
00:39:10,182 --> 00:39:16,446
now, till you have to make the lights, you
had to work hard, make the lights, put them

